{
    "analysis": "The Executor computed anomaly_summary for metric.csv in the incident window (2020-05-26 02:00–02:30 Asia/Shanghai) and found 20 (cmdb_id,kpi_name) groups flagged as anomalous. Many top groups are DB-level KPIs (db_001..db_004) and node Disk_io_util (os_010, os_017). However, numerous groups show count_high and count_low equal to the window size because global_p95 == global_p5 (constant or nearly-constant series), which is a thresholding artifact and should not be treated as meaningful high/low anomalies. We therefore cannot yet trust these groups as genuine faults. Next, we must filter out these constant-series artifacts before doing consecutive-fault (sub-series) detection and severity estimation.",
